magpie.data.utilities.filters

Class PhaseDiagramExclusionFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.filters.BaseDatasetFilter
      • magpie.data.utilities.filters.ContainsElementFilter
        • magpie.data.utilities.filters.PhaseDiagramExclusionFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Options

    public class PhaseDiagramExclusionFilter
extends ContainsElementFilter
    Filter entries from certain phase diagrams. Removes entries that only contain elements from a certain set and those that contain all elements from that set.

    Example: When excluding entries from the Al-Ni phase diagram

    1. Al will be removed because it contains Al and no other element
    2. AlNi will be removed because it contains both Al and Ni
    3. AlZr will not be removed because it contains another element
    4. AlNiZr will be removed because it contains both Al and Ni

    Usage: <Element names...>
    Element names...: Entries containing these elements pass the filter

    See Also:
